<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!-- Hardened runtime: tighten by default. JIT and unsigned exec memory are
         disabled because we don't run a JIT (Rust is AOT) and don't load
         arbitrary code at runtime. Disabling these reduces attack surface. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <false/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <false/>
    <!-- Library validation is OFF (false here = "do not disable validation"
         = validation stays enabled). Only Apple-signed or same-team-signed
         dylibs may load. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <false/>

    <!-- Networking: relay HTTP client + daemon IPC socket (Unix socket is
         not gated, but server entitlement is required if we ever bind TCP). -->
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.network.server</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- File access: user-selected files only (e.g. drag-drop, file picker).
         App sandbox is OFF because the clipboard daemon needs full disk
         access semantics (read pasteboard, write history DB outside
         container) and we are not shipping via Mac App Store. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <false/>

    <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
         Keychain ThisDeviceOnly hardening (Fix C — DO NOT enable under
         ad-hoc signing).

         The daemon tries to re-store the X25519 device-secret key with
         `kSecAttrAccessibleWhenUnlockedThisDeviceOnly` so it never syncs to
         iCloud Keychain (see keychain/mod.rs `set_generic_password_locked_down`).
         Building a `SecAccessControl` with that accessibility requires the
         app to carry a `keychain-access-groups` entitlement. When it is
         absent, `SecItemAdd`/`SecItemUpdate` returns errSecMissingEntitlement
         (-34018, "A required entitlement isn't present") and the daemon logs
         the "could not migrate device key to ThisDeviceOnly accessibility"
         warning. The code now degrades gracefully on that exact error (the
         key stays fully usable; only the iCloud-sync suppression is skipped).

         CONSTRAINT: an entitlement like the one below is ONLY honored by the
         OS when the binary is signed with a real Apple **Developer ID**
         certificate whose team prefix matches the access-group string
         (e.g. "$(TeamIdentifierPrefix)com.copypaste.daemon"). Ad-hoc
         signatures (`codesign` with the ad-hoc `-` identity, which is what
         this project uses; see .github/workflows/release.yml) CANNOT carry a usable
         keychain-access-group: there is no team identifier to anchor it to,
         and shipping it under ad-hoc signing can break keychain access
         entirely. It is therefore left COMMENTED OUT here on purpose.

         To fully fix ThisDeviceOnly hardening, the release must switch to
         Developer-ID signing and UNCOMMENT the block below (substituting the
         real team prefix). This needs a real signed build + install to verify.

    <key>keychain-access-groups</key>
    <array>
        <string>$(TeamIdentifierPrefix)com.copypaste.daemon</string>
    </array>
         ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
</dict>
</plist>
